org.logicmill.util.concurrent

Class ConcurrentHashMapProbe.SegmentIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.logicmill.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMapProbe.SegmentIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<ConcurrentHashMapProbe.SegmentProbe>
    Enclosing class:
    ConcurrentHashMapProbe

    public class ConcurrentHashMapProbe.SegmentIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<ConcurrentHashMapProbe.SegmentProbe>
    An iterator over segments in the map associated with this probe object. Segments are represented by, and made visible through, ConcurrentHashMapProbe.SegmentProbe proxy objects. The iterator guarantees that each segment is exposed through a probe returned by next() at most once, and that the set of segments exposed by the iterator will not contain overlapping entry sets. The set of segments exposed by next() will contain all of the entries that are in the map at the time the iterator is created, and are not removed before the iterator is exhausted. A map entry will appear in at most one segment exposed by next().
    Author:
    David Curtis
